name: v0.7.0
body:
## What's Changed

* secretservice: list wraps the error from secretservice_linux.c. by @QiWang19 in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/191
* secretservice: fix return values in List() in secretservice_linux.go by @alakesh in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/211
* pass: return an error when a cred doesn't exist by @nicks in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/221
* pass: macOS build support by @ellsclytn in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/169
* registryurl: remove fallback code for go < 1.8 by @thaJeztah in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/225
* vendor: bump github.com/danieljoos/wincred to v1.1.2 by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/208
* vendor: golang.org/x/sys v0.0.0-20220825204002-c680a09ffe64 by @thaJeztah in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/238
* chore: Dockerfile for cross compilation by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/219
* chore: Dockerfile debian based build by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/239
* chore: test stage and ci jobs by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/224
* chore: update to go 1.18.5 by @thaJeztah in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/226
* chore: support linux/ppc64le and linux/s390x cross build by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/227
* chore: vendor validation by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/230
* chore: lint gha job and remove travis by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/231
* chore: simplify "go build" commands by @thaJeztah in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/232
* chore: update local build instructions in README by @thaJeztah in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/233
* chore: use relative paths in Makefile for "go build" by @ZauberNerd in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/236
* chore: set version and revision at linked time by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/234
* chore: release target with checksums by @crazy-max in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/237

## New Contributors

* @QiWang19 made their first contribution in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/191
* @alakesh made their first contribution in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/211
* @crazy-max made their first contribution in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/208
* @ellsclytn made their first contribution in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/169
* @ZauberNerd made their first contribution in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/236
* @nicks made their first contribution in https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/pull/221

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/compare/v0.6.4...v0.7.0

name: v0.6.3
body: * Fix a double free in the List functions. See https://github.com/docker/docker-credential-helpers/commit/87c80bfba583eadc087810d17aa631ef4e405efc

name: v0.6.2
body:
- Better initialization check in `Pass`
- Trim pass show output in `Pass`
- Only init on run, and do so lazily in `Pass`
- Changed the way for checking if password-store is initalized in `Pass`
- Make docker-credential-wincred work like docker-credential-osxkeychain
- Fix docker-credential-osxkeychain list behaviour in case of missing entry in keychain

### Note

`Go` v1.12.x compatibility
`osxkeychain` for macOS 10.11 compatibility

name: v0.6.0
body:
- New credential helper on Linux using `pass`
- New entry point for passing environment variables when calling a credential helper
- Add a Makefile rule generating a Windows release binary

### Note

`pass` needs to be configured for `docker-credential-pass` to work properly.
It must be initialized with a `gpg2` key ID. Make sure your GPG key exists in `gpg2` keyring as `pass` uses `gpg2` instead of the default `gpg`.

name: v0.5.2
body:
- Add a `version` command to output the version
- Fix storing URLs without scheme on OSX, and use `https://` by default

name: v0.5.1
body:
* Redirect credential helpers' standard error to the caller's
* Prevent invalid credentials and credentials queries

name: v0.5.0
body: - Add a label for Docker credentials and filter credentials lookup to filter keychain lookups

name: v0.4.2
body:
- Fix osxkeychain list
- macOS binary is now signed on release
- Generate a `.exe` instead

name: v0.4.1
body: * Fixes to support older version of OSX (10.10, 10.11)

name: v0.4.0
body:
* Full implementation for OSX ready
* Fix some windows issues
* Implement client.List, change list API
* mac: delete credentials before adding them to avoid already exist error (fixes #37)

name: v0.3.0
body: * Add Go client library to talk with the native programs

name: v0.2.0
body:
* Initial release of docker-credential-secretservice for Linux
* Use new secrets payload introduced in https://github.com/moby/moby/pull/20970

name: v0.1.0
body:
* Initial release of docker-credential-osxkeychain for Mac OS X
* Initial release of docker-credential-wincred for Microsoft Windows
